caption: Good ramen, gyoza, and salad, but the rock shrimp stole the show. Cooked perfectly and just a little sweet. We had a second order for dessert.
Good ambience, good food, overall I come out as a happy camper eating at Jinya!
A good place to visit
tanaka ramen is great!  Love Terrance the chef!
Delicious and fast service
This is the one of the best ramen places ijn chicago!

The ramen was ok, nothing special. But our rice dish was cold and the waitress has to take it back to the kitchen and we can hear they pop it in the mircowave to heat it up. That's not how you heat up rice and keep it moist and soft.

This place is NOT open from 11am to 10pm. They close in between lunch and dinner but this isn't listed anywhere. I walked all the way there with my family of 6 only to see a big "CLOSED" sign. Google and their website utterly failed at communicating this.

I am not an expert on ramen but I thought that the ramen here tasted really good.  They have several different options for ramen and different broths. Service was good too. Visited here during lunch time but it wasn’t too crowded.
Pretty good!
Good Ramen

Really wanted to like this place,but it was a weird experience.  A table that ordered after us got their food before us.  When our food finally arrived, it was only my friend's bowl. Waited another 10 mins for mine.  Finally arrives, but after 4 bites I find a plastic twist tie in my food - it was black and blended in with the funky mushrooms. Wth?  Again, waitress apologizes profusely offers to replace but by now I'm so turned off, we get our bill and leave.  Pretty sure I won't go again, lol.
Really good food but in reality, it was expensive ramen noodles.
Good ramen, good prices, good service. I will absolutely be going here again.
Decent food. Slightly pricey

What is not to love about Jinya?! I was first introduced to this in LV, and I became an instant fan. Was truly happy to find out there was one in Chicago when I was making travel plans. I was not disappointed! Kind employees, great ramen, and a nice atmosphere. I had the spicy creamy vegan ramen which was delicious. What blew my mind was the brussel sprout tempura. Omg!! I never thought I'd be a fan of brussel sprouts, but I definitely loved this. Give it a try...it's a must!
Awesome spot for authentic Japanese ramen! Spicy Tonkatsu and pork gyoza were delicious.
Spicy chicken ramen and spicy umami miso were clutch
Best chicken broth ramen in Chicago
Very good.
Great ramen
Great food. Service could be better. I will visit again
Quality ramen at an excellent price. Forget about waiting in line for an hour in Wicker park, come here for fast and friendly service and great food.
Love their weekly special and the cauliflower appetizer.
Tasty ramen
Genuine Japanese Raman. You can ask for thick or thin noodles. Would've been better if it instructs guests to chooser hardness of noodles as well. (Noodles to soft for my personal preference

Cosy, modern ramen joint with a great variety of options; pork, chicken, vegetables bases with tons of additional options like corn, eggs, leeks, garlic, etc. Both thick and thin noodle options. Highly mutable spice level with mild, spicy and hot.  Good array of drinks though I did not get to sample any food time around.  Despite being quite busy on a Friday evening, the food was excellent, noodles were sublime and the flavors of my tonkatsu pork ramen with extra egg and garlic all mixed wonderfully.

I was disappointed by the food here. The base of my ramen didn’t have much flavor and the hot sauce canisters on both my table and the one next to it were completely empty. I wouldn’t go here again; there’s better ramen in the city.
Delicious and authentic food. We had the gyoza, and I tried the Sprouting Up Ramen. Both were fantastic. Nice atmosphere, will definitely be back!
Vegetarian and want Ramen? This is the place!
Loved it. The spicy ramen was the best. Looking for it in Florida. Staff was nice and friendly. Recommended.

Appetizers left much to be desired, though the ramen was quite good. Unfortunately, the service was terrible. With a plethora of other ramen joints popping up around the city, this one wouldn't be my first recommendation.
They changed noodles and reduced bowl size. Not good anymore which is a real shame
The ramen soup is not overly salty and the noodles are still under al denete but overall, good.

Ramen was good, not great. They were out of onsen eggs as well as their only cider (that I saw). The takoyaki we ordered was really great, and the crispy chicken we ordered was good but very lukewarm. Service was slow at every step but it was a busy Saturday night so it’s probably expected. Overall - good place to go if you’re in the area and really craving a piping hot bowl of ramen, but both the service and food could be improved.
I’m probably a bit of a ramen snob, but the ramen here was just okay - especially compared to places like High Five. Really loved the takoyaki though! Just expected slightly better ramen.
Love the ramen here and they offer a lot of options to add items to your bowl of ramen.
Good. Eat here. Bad music. Food makes up for it.
My favorite ramen place in the city! Affordable prices, quick service and friendly staff.
Kitchen closed at 9:35?... then why say open until 10. BS.

Lackluster food is one thing and well I wasn't expecting anything spectacular anyways. I just wanted dinner, and this place was close to home. I was feeling somewhat under the weather and thought Ramen might be a good choice.  Service was absolutely mediocre. I felt like I was being punished somehow for even coming into the restaurant at all.  I am a full time server at a restaurant myself so I understand how terrible customers could be but this is at the end of the day the job we chose to do.  I felt rushed, server offered no suggestions, and was incredibly unfriendly and cold throughout my entire experience.  I will not be coming back.

Although the food at this place is extraordinary, and has been a favorite of ours, we were rudely treated this past Saturday night due to a confusion about closing time.  Their website reads 12 midnight on Saturday, when they close at 10.  We got there at 9:50 expecting a relaxing dinner.  The cook was angry that we ordered, slamming things around, no one attending to our order for drinks until we received out food, when the cook was done the lights were literally shut off and we were rushed to pay before we were finished eating.  Very un-hospitable.

Overall, a moderately expensive trendy place to eat.  Has a cool setting with decent options for food.  I tried their ramen, and honestly it wasn't as flavorful as I was hoping.  I much prefer furious spoon.  However, I had a great time and it was fun to bring some friends.

I've ordered from Jinya many times. Their creamy vegan ramen is excellent. However, I've been waiting for weeks to have their green beans and cashews (they were off the menu for a while). Finally, when they were back, I ordered two sides of green beans ($4.80 each). Thank goodness I did - each "side" only containes about 10-15 beans. They looked sad and were way over priced. Taste was just ok. Looking forward to other ramen places opening in East Lakeview soon.
Good food, atmosphere is a little confusing... Techno music with sports blasting on tv
Overall great place with reasonable prices. Takoyaki was great. Cha Cha Cha was great.

Imagine ramen, a cool and hip trend nowadays, was served by your really boring parents. This ramen joint gets the product right for the most part, especially serving broth that isn't super salty, as compared by some other ramen planned that have people waiting in line bc of all the"buzz", but the atmosphere on a Friday evening in August is comparable to when a party is over and you walk in on the staff cleaning up. This restaurant is open, there are people on the street, but no one is eating here. They have good food but bad advertising.
Kids meal were nice and big enough, the noodle soup as genuine as I tastes, and they even don't accept any reservation!
Fast service, nice food!
Cha Cha Cha, must try. Garlic ramen with porky belly.
Food an drinks were very tasty and reasonably priced. Will definitely be back.
Great ramen. When they say it's spicy they really mean it.
Mediocre food
Absolutely delish mmmm! A must try to anyone who loves ramen...
I want seasonal special ramen to be renewed more frequently.
Have been here multiple times and always bring friends.
Great service & even better food!
Curry rice has no beef or chicken or anything! But the taste is good… so confused

DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE! Delivery takes nearly two hours when they said it would be 45 to 60 minutes and upon calling to ask that be remedied they did nothing and I was very polite and rarely leave reviews.. Also side note.. it isn't worth the money the noodles taste like the packaged ramen you get in the store and the pork ramen comes with one piece and you are given instructions to cook it.. I love cooking but order out so I didn't have to for a night lol plus noodles were in a big glob upon arrival.. for 13.80 you should atleast get the standard three pieces oh and the egg was no where near soft boiled. .. I mean come on. There are way better ramen places in the area and close by go there! :)

Don't order online. You will be wasting your time and money. Suggested delivery time is 45-60 minutes. I didn't get my food until 1 hr and 30 mins later, after I called and reminded them I was still waiting.  Also, they did not have the driver's number to contact or locate, so when I asked how much longer, they couldn't answer.  Overall, just a terrible experience, received luke warm ramen, with what felt like an inadequate amount of pork.
Good food bad service.
Great cozy place
Jinya Ramen soup and salmon tacos were amazing!!
Tasty and not too crowded
Great ramen, try the tonkotsu white!
This is definitely my favorite ramen place in Linkin park.
Good food, unless u know nothing about how ramen should taste.
Solid ramen, surprisingly good dumplings.
Decent food, nice place to sit and enjoy dinner and drinks with friends. Friendly staff
Fantastic ramen (especially tokontsu black) but mind-numbingly bad music. Why play loud EDM all the time? Why?
Come here just for the spicy creamy vegan ramen!
The broth is so flavorful!

Ramen came out lukewarm. Was expecting some black garlic oil which really would have made this bowl excel. Otherwise, it's a decent bowl but lacks depth or character. Service was great and the ambiance relaxed.
This place has some delicious ramen. I ordered the Spicy Chicken Ramen and did the "spicy" level (there was mild, spicy, and hot to choose from) and I would highly recommend.

Great food. I took my boyfriend here due to the fact he loves Ramen and we had a extremely good dinner and enjoyed ourselves. They also offer a menu with a few cool grownup beverages. Good meals at an affordable rate whilst making the area sense very secure and first-rate
Very solid Ramen. Actually liked it more than Furious Spoon.
Had very good ramen, and during the height of the Pokemon Go craze even ran related promotions.
The ramen is so good here and they have really yummy unique apps like kimchi tacos!

What a disappointing meal. My friend and I made reservations Friday night and couldn't get in until 9pm and when we walked up the place was almost dead.  We both shared the cheese combo plate. The cheeses we picked were good but literally we only had a bite or 2 each. It had to be the smallest cheese plate I have ever had. Next we had the suya beef because the written description sounded so good. The taste was awful!! It tasted like leather and we both took a bite and could not eat it. I asked to return it immediately. Lastly, we tried the angus beef sliders. No flavor or sauce to add. It was the driest slider I have ever had. My friend actually joked that it didn't taste like beef but tasted like horse. We had a nice laugh though over our meal. We ended up having to spend more money elsewhere to eat as we were still super hungry after our poor choices and did not want to pay more to them for bad food. Also they do not have any type of risotto!! Huge disappointment since it is on their online menu.  The plus parts would be the server, he was super smily and friendly and the 3oz wine pours. Still pricey but they have a good selection of wines. For that 2 stars is given instead of 1.
Mediocre service and I had to get stitches from a broken chair in their restaurant.
$2 extra for mushrooms and they're just a few white button mushies. Ramen could have been served a bit hotter too.

Black tonkatsu was good but slightly off on flavor and bit spicy: the chili oil was all in one spot, so a bit shocking. The white ramen was very good. It's a bit off-putting that they charge for all their extras, but it gives some flexibility. The service was suspect, despite the place being empty.
Get the Tonkatsu Black or the Shio Ramen. Their broth is so, so good.

Ramem was well made and satisfying. Curry and rice as an appetizer as well as salad with a dressing that was a bit garlic and ginger, which should not be missed if you enjoy those flavors. Only downside were the out of order restrooms.

A fantastic place to come to warm up on a cold windy day. First time here and tried their Jinya Chicken Ramen. Great price with a good portion where it will leave you comfortably full (and not feel like you are going to explode). Aside the servers taking a little while to get our order, the food came out fairly quickly. Will definitely return.

I ordered food from Jinya Ramen for delivery. I received cold food that actually required me to heat it up in a Microwave. I ordered food for delivery to avoid the cooking process. There was no mention of having to cook the food on the website I ordered from. I called the restaurant to   complain, and the person I spoke to admitted the error, but did not apologize and was quite frankly rude about the situation. I would never order from them again, or visit the restaurant, as the member of staff I spoke to was very unprofessional.
Very slow service, seems very understaffed.. seems like a lot of traffic so maybe the food is just that good,  too long of a wait for me to find out though
Best vegan ramen!
$5 corkage fee per person and you won't open my wine or poor my glass or give an ice bucket. I usually prefer to eat before getting ....
Pretty darn good ramen

The service was good but the Ramen was very mediocre. I have had Jinya at their location in Austin and it was great but this location was just ok. Might have just been an off night so probably will try again since I have had better experiences at some of their other locations
Delicious food and great service
God food. World Series game 7 all other restaurants at full capacity. Came here, not disappointed at all.
I wasn't the biggest fan. It was a bit lukewarm by the time I got it which might have influenced the taste, but it was just okay.

Best ramen in Lakview. Not sure about other neighborhoods because I'm perfectly satisfied with Jinya' delicous ramen right where I live and don't need to look elsewhere. I have had other ramen in the area and there is no comparison. Jinya is the best.
Pretty good ramen
Friendly and Inviting, Ramen was delicious.
Ate with friends, as soon as it turned 10. They turned all the lights on and blasted rap music. Thanks for warm inviting feeling...
Very attentive staff. Broth was good, but served luke warm this visit. Prefer the thick noodles, recommend picking options that use those over then thin. Garlic lover one is my favorite.
Place was seriously understaffed, with only one server. Will probably order take out next time.

good ramen. didn't blow me away though. the broth just didn't have anything unique about it. prices for additional ingredients are not cheap. I'm not a ramen snob though. just didn't like the ramen enough given the price.
A must go place absolutely love their ramen. No comparison. Honestly best ramen I've had since coming back from Japan!
Just okay..

It's a Sunday afternoon and that may be part of the problem but it was pretty eh.  I got the chef special. The ramen felt like it had been sitting for a while. The egg wasn't really close to soft boiled. The overall tempature of the whole piece wasn't quite where it needed to be. The most disappointing part is that overall the flavor wasn't very strong.  However at $15 with tax it's something I'd be willing to try again during peak hours to see if some of the other reviewers are right and I landed here on a bad night.
Top three spot for ramen in Chicago, tons of varieties puts them ahead of many tonkotsu focused places.  Also don't miss out on the takoyaki and the tempura.
The inside of this place is nicely decorated. The menu had a variety of ramen to choose from.  I would recommend this place for small groups and would visit again.

Modern, fusiony ramen bar in Lakeview/Lincoln Park area. It's going for the trendy feel so I didn't expect the food to be very authentic. The ramen was pretty good - I got the special of the day: chicken broth with fried brussels sprouts. It was pretty good. The eggplant miso was disappointing - too greasy and too sweet.
Really good ramen and nice service. By far my favorite ramen in town.
Great food! They play really bad dance music though. That's the only downside.

Jinya Ramen Bar upholds traditional ramen noodle standards, which is apparent in their rich flavors and fresh ingredients. Bowls are extremely customizable, and there are plenty of Asian-style tapas to pair with main dishes. Give their cold ramen a try for a very different ramen experience. Prices are extremely affordable, but Jinya has been known to run Groupons for additional savings! Keep an eye out.
Pricey. Wasabi ramen better. Or better yet, mitsua in the suburbs
Food was good and it's BYOB. I did think there may have been too much MSGs in their food.
The noodles are delicious.

I've been to at least 6 ramen places in Chicago and Jinya is my favorite so far.  Broths are incredibly well seasoned and flavorful, not too oily or greasy.  I judge ramen places by their noodles, and I love how Jinya's noodles are chewy and tender.  They stand out from a lot of the other ramen places that serve noodles that are too starchy and chalky.  They have a large variety of ramen options and are also reasonably priced (not like many other places that charge around $16 a bowl).  Tip: Try the gyoza appetizer.
Awesome service and BYOB! Prices are reasonable and ramen was excellent. Fried chicken was a bit undercooked (yikes) but that's why it got docked 1 star. Overall, good food and good service.
Great BYOB location in LP. Spicy Chicken with extra noodles and a seasoned egg is my favorite.

The spicy chicken ramen was outstanding, crave for it everyday, and their hot sauce is hotter than the hottest wing sauce you've tasted! Pork was 4/5 but I'd rate this 5 just for the chicken experience.
Excellent Ramen
Impressive ramen house.
VERY TASTY. BEST IN CHI TOWN!!
Fantastic ramen with a bit of uniqueness added to it. 5 stars!
So so ramen maybe it will get better
Loved the place.   Great service and some of the best food we have had.  Easy too get to.
Delicious place and the owner was very friendly and flexible.
